  "texts": [
    "Indeed, I(θ, S) depends on the distribution of the sample S that is unknown in practice.",
    "In order to use (6.5), one must upper bound I(θ, S) by a quantity that does not depend on the sample.",
    "• Catoni (2007, page 14 and 51) discuss the optimization of PAC-Bayes bounds with respect to the prior.",
    "In order to explain the discussion done there, apply √ ab ≤ a/(2λ) + bλ/2 to (6.6) to get a \"Catoni style\" bound:",
    "r(θ)] ≤ Cλ 2n + E S [KL(ρ∥π)] λ and thus E S E θ∼ρ [R(θ)] ≤ E S E θ∼ρ [r(θ)] + Cλ 2n + KL(ρ∥π) λ (compare to Theorem 2.8 above)."
  ],
